                       "message":  "W08-4-RETIRE-SHADOW: retire the shadowed EditorKeyCommand File/Edit binds; re-anchor the parity guard\n\nFinal carve of the accelerator-execution thread. After the W08.3 cutover (#310)\nthe EditorKeyCommand::{Undo, Redo, Save, SaveAsProject} variants were SHADOWS —\nthe keyboard reached them no longer (the menu path caught Ctrl+Z/Y/S/Shift+S\nfirst), and their keystroke-\u003ecommand literals were DUPLICATED between\nfrom_key_press (commands.rs) and default_editor_menu (editor-ui). This removes the\nduplication: the File/Edit accelerators now live ONLY in the canonical menu.\n\nEditorKeyCommand is KEPT (not renamed) for the execution-only time-scale binds\n(Ctrl+2/0/4), which have no menu home and are not duplicated. Pure de-duplication\n— no runtime behaviour change (the menu path already does exactly what the retired\nvariants did; W08.3 proved equivalence).\n\nProduction:\n- commands.rs: remove the Undo/Redo/Save/SaveAsProject variants + their\n  from_key_press arms (drop the Ctrl+Shift block) + their handle_key_command arms.\n  from_key_press now returns Some only for Ctrl+2/0/4; handle_key_command dispatches\n  only the three time-scale binds. Docs updated. (BusError import retained — still\n  used by submit_action/undo_command/redo_command.)\n\nParity guard re-anchor (accelerator.rs):\n- keyboard_map_and_menu_agree_on_shared_accelerators now drives all FIVE File/Edit\n  binds (Ctrl+O/S/Shift+S/Z/Y) via keycode_to_shortcut -\u003e command_for_shortcut and\n  asserts (a) the menu binds each to its Command and (b) from_key_press returns None\n  for each (the retirement holds; no shadow can drift). The time-scale block\n  (from_key_press Some, menu None) is unchanged. Module header + from_key_press doc\n  refreshed (from_key_press is the time-scale executor, no longer a shared-bind\n  anchor).\n\nTest migration (the retirement broke every EditorKeyCommand::{Undo,Redo,Save}\nsite — full consumer census, NOT a sample):\n- keyboard_command_bus_round_trip.rs: deleted 4 EditorKeyCommand-driven behaviour\n  tests (exact duplicates of the W08.3 route_menu_command tests), migrated 3\n  unique-coverage tests (redo-empty / undo-after-all-undone / three-round-trips) to\n  route_menu_command, updated the 2 from_key_press guards (Ctrl+Z/Y/S + Ctrl+Shift+S\n  now -\u003e None), refreshed the header.\n- time_scale_test.rs: migrated 6 Undo/Redo sites to route_menu_command (SetTimeScale*\n  sites unchanged); +file-level Command import; dropped 2 now-unused local imports.\n- inspector_snapshot_smoke.rs: migrated the Undo/Redo round-trip to route_menu_command.\n- lifecycle/tests.rs: migrated the Ctrl+S Save test to route_menu_command; repurposed\n  the Ctrl+Shift+S decode test to pin from_key_press returning None for the retired\n  binds.\n\nStale-prose / broken-link sweep:\n- editor-ui default_menu.rs: inverted the header — the menu is the CANONICAL source\n  now (was \"mirrors EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press\").\n- editor-shell save_request.rs: rewrote the broken intra-doc links\n  [Save](EditorKeyCommand::Save)/[SaveAsProject](...) to the route_menu_command path.\n- editor-egui-host lib.rs: updated the egui-consumed example handler reference.\n\nNo Cargo/edge change, no menu-definition change, no rename. 9 files, -139 net lines.\nGate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints; editor-shell (226 lib + integration) +\neditor-ui tests pass.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
