                       "message":  "W08-4-RETIRE-SHADOW: correct stale shadow-map prose (doc/comment-only)\n\nCodex review on #311: no functional blocker (retired variants gone from live\nreferences, EditorKeyCommand is time-scale-only, parity guard re-anchored\ncorrectly), but stale LIVE prose still described the old shadow map. Comment/doc\nonly — no code/test logic change.\n\nCodex-listed files:\n- commands.rs: module header EditorKeyCommand set (Ctrl+Z/Y/S -\u003e the Ctrl+2/0/4\n  time-scale binds); undo_command/redo_command/submit_action docs now point the\n  NothingToUndo/Redo swallow at route_menu_command, not the (retired) keyboard\n  handler arms.\n- lifecycle/mod.rs: window_event playback fall-through comment reflects the new\n  ladder order (menu lookup -\u003e EditorKeyCommand time-scale -\u003e playback); the\n  time-scale fallback comment drops the \"shadowed until W08.4 retires them\"\n  wording (W08.4 retired them).\n- render_path.rs: route_menu_command doc + the Edit Undo/Redo arm comment no\n  longer frame the menu as \"behaviour-identical to the Ctrl+Z/Y bus path /\n  exactly as handle_key_command does\" (the keystrokes resolve THROUGH this\n  method now).\n- playback.rs: module header dispatch-lane description (EditorKeyCommand is the\n  time-scale lane; File/Edit go via the menu) + the test-coverage reference\n  (keyboard_command_bus_round_trip.rs drives route_menu_command, not\n  handle_key_command).\n- editor-egui-host/menu_tests.rs: the accelerator-display comment (menu is the\n  canonical source, not a mirror of EditorKeyCommand).\n\nCompleteness sweep (whole class, not just the flagged spots) also fixed:\n- menu_tests.rs: two \"no accelerator display yet (deferred with W08 execution)\"\n  assertion messages -\u003e Play uses the plain Space/Escape PIE binds (W08 is done;\n  Play has no menu accelerator by design).\n\nDated history (mod.rs \"# 2026-05-21 Phase 9 ...\" section) left as-is per the\ndated-references-stay rule. fmt clean; editor-shell (226 lib + integration) +\neditor-egui-host tests pass.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
