                       "message":  "W08-4-RETIRE-SHADOW: correct stale parity-guard \"lockstep\" prose (doc-only)\n\nCodex re-review on #311: two live comments still framed the parity guard as\nkeeping from_key_press / the keyboard map \"in lockstep\" with the menu. Post-W08.4\nthe invariant is different — the menu is canonical for the File/Edit binds and\nfrom_key_press intentionally returns None for those five, so no shadow remains to\nkeep \"in sync\".\n\n- lifecycle/mod.rs (window_event ladder comment): \"the parity guard keeps\n  from_key_press and the menu in lockstep\" -\u003e \"pins that the menu binds these five\n  accelerators while from_key_press returns None for them (no shadow remains)\".\n- render_path.rs (route_menu_command doc): \"the parity guard locks the keyboard\n  map to the same menu, so a keystroke and its menu item dispatch the identical\n  Command\" -\u003e a keystroke and its menu item dispatch the identical Command because\n  both resolve through the same canonical menu; the guard pins from_key_press no\n  longer shadows these binds.\n\nWhole-class re-grep (lockstep / locks the keyboard / in sync / agree / diverge)\nfinds no other stale parity-framing in editor-shell. Comment-only; fmt clean.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
